250 g Ground Beef
170 g Spaghetti
1 unit(s) Shanghai Bok Choy
28 g Peanuts, chopped
1 tbsp Chili-Garlic Sauce
2 unit(s) Peanut Butter
2 tbsp Sweet Chili Sauce
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
2 tbsp Spicy Mayo
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
0.13 tsp Pepper*
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*

Add spaghetti to the boiling water.
Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 10-12 min.
Reserve 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) pasta water, then drain noodles.

Meanwhile, cut bok choy into 1-inch pieces.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/2-inch pieces.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Whisk together sweet chili sauce, peanut butter, soy sauce, chili-garlic sauce and reserved pasta water in a medium bowl.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
When hot, add peanuts to the dry pan. Toast, stirring often, until golden-brown, 4-5 min. ( TIP: Keep your eye on peanuts so they don't burn!)
Transfer to a plate.

Reheat the same pan over medium. Add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef and garlic.
Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Season with salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, combine spicy mayo and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) water in a small bowl.

Add peppers and bok choy to the pan with beef. Cook, stirring often, until veggies are tender-crisp, 2-4 min.
Add noodles and sauce. Cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens slightly and coats noodles, 2-4 min.
Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

Divide s picy beef and peanut dragon noodles between bowls.
Drizzle spicy mayo over top, to taste.
Sprinkle with peanuts.

If you've opted to get beef, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the pork.